NEW YORK Police Commits
sioner Michael ]. Murphy ap-
pointed Capt. Lloyd George Sealy
as the first Negro to command a
police precinct in Harlem.


This met one of the demands
of Negro leaders during recent
Harlem riots.


Capt. Sealy is the only Negro
precinct commander in the city
at this time. The only other
previous Negro precinct head
was the late Deputy Chief In
spector George Redding, who was
promoted in 1886.


The new precinct commander
is AZ years old and has been on
the force for FL years. He
is one of three Negro captains
on the entire police force.


The captain was born in Man
haitian, his parents we're natives
of Barbados, West Indies. He
is named for Britain's prime
minister during World War l.


He attended Brooklyn College
after being one of a dozen Negroes
to graduate from predominantly
white Jefferson High School in
1884.


After two years he became
federal messenger in Washington
and later railway clerk. In
1912, he joined the plice force
as a patrolman.


Captain Sealy returned to col
lege in the l95Os and earned his
law degree from Brooklyn Law
School. Last year he attended
the National Academy of the
Federal Bureau of Investigation.


He was promoted to his cap
taincy last November.

Salt River Project is ranked
among the five top reclamation
projects in the nation for crop
production, with a cumulative
value of almost two billion dol
lars since its beginning.


Records of the u. S. Bureau of
Reclamation show the project has
irrigated crops valued at total
of ST. .9O8 900. 900 since 1906.


Crops produced by farmers on
project-irrigated lands last year
accounted for $53 ,63O.7l4 of the
total. This represents an in
crease in crop value of almost
100000 over 1862.


The average gross crop value
per acre in 1868 was 1854, as
compared to $295.74 per acre in
1862.


The increase is attributed to
more intensified farming. double
cropping and more emphasis on
cash crops.


Salt River Project has playeda
prime role in boosting Maricopa
County to third place among the
top 400 leading agricultural coun-
ties in the Nation in gross farm
income. First and second place
went to Fresno and Kern Counties
in California.


The average production Of in
dividual farms places Arizona
tops in the nation.

tinuing nutrition education and
research programs, supported by
all segments of the dairy in
dustry. have further strengthened
this market for milk and other
healthful foods.
